                'media_used' => '',
                'biography' => '<p>Joan Carlile, a British portrait painter, was born around 1606. She was one of the first women in England to make a career as a professional artist. In 1626, she married the poet Lodowick Carlile and the couple lived primarily in London. Beginning in the 1640s, Carlile began to make a name for herself as a portraitist. Few of her works survive. She died in 1679.</p>',
