                'media_used' => '',
                'biography' => '<p>Presumed to have been born in Antwerp, Volcxken Diericx was an important print publisher active in the city in the sixteenth century. In 1647, she married the print publisher Hieronymus Cock. Following her husband’s death in 1570, Diericx took over their publishing house Aux Quatre Vents, and published numerous prints until her death in 1600.</p>',
