                'active_locations' => 'The Netherlands',
                'media_used' => '',
                'biography' => '<p>Gesina ter Borch was active as a watercolorist during the Dutch Golden Age. Although she was born in Deventer, she was baptized in Zwolle and spent most of her life there. She came from an artistic family, with many of her immediate family members making careers as professional artists. Gesina worked primarily as an amateur artist, rather than producing works for sale. Many of her works, which are small in scale, are housed in albums.</p>',
